HEADWORD: Wallower
<hw>Wal"low*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, wallows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A lantern wheel; a
trundle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wallowish</ent>⟦br⟧
